\id NUM - Wycliffe’s Bible Modern Spelling Enhanced, Word Files Text Conversion and standardization, A. Camus 05 2019
\h NUMBERS
\toc1 NUMBERS
\toc2 Numbers
\toc3 NUM
\mt1 NUMBERS
\c 1
\cl CHAPTER 1
\p 
\v 1 And the Lord spake to Moses in the desert of Sinai, in the tabernacle of the bond of peace\f + \fr 1:1 \ft In Numbers, the Tabernacle is often called ‘the tabernacle of the bond of peace’, that is, ‘the Tabernacle of the Covenant’; in the rest of the Old Testament of the “\bk Wycliffe Bible\bk*”, it is usually referred to as ‘the tabernacle of (the) witnessing’.\f*, in the first day of the second month, in the tother year of their going out of Egypt, and said, \sls (And the Lord spoke to Moses in the Sinai Desert, in the Tabernacle of the Covenant, \em that is, the Tabernacle of the Witnessing\em*, on the first day of the second month, in the second year of their going out of Egypt, and said,)\sls*
\p 
\v 2 Take ye the sum, \em or the number\em*, of all the congregation of the sons of Israel, by their kindreds, and families, and all their names each by themselves, whatever thing of male kind, \sls (Take ye the sum, \em or the number\em*, of all the congregation of the people of Israel, by their kindreds, and families, and list, \em or register\em*, all their names, whoever is a male,)\sls*
\p 
\v 3 from the twentieth year and above, of all the strong men of Israel, \sls (or from twenty years of age and older, of all the strong men in Israel)\sls*; and thou and Aaron shall number them by their companies.
\p 
\v 4 And the princes of the lineages \sls (or And the leaders of the tribes)\sls*, and of the families, in their kindreds, shall be with you,
\p 
\v 5 of which \em princes\em*, these be the names, \sls (or of which \em leaders\em*, these be the names)\sls*; of Reuben, Elizur, the son of Shedeur;
\p 
\v 6 of Simeon, Shelumiel, the son of Zurishaddai;
\p 
\v 7 of Judah, Nahshon, the son of Amminadab;
\p 
\v 8 of Issachar, Nethaneel, the son of Zuar;
\p 
\v 9 of Zebulun, Eliab, the son of Helon;
\p 
\v 10 soothly of the sons of Joseph; of Ephraim, Elishama, the son of Ammihud; of Manasseh, Gamaliel, the son of Pedahzur;
\p 
\v 11 of Benjamin, Abidan, the son of Gideoni;
\p 
\v 12 of Dan, Ahiezer, the son of Ammishaddai;
\p 
\v 13 of Asher, Pagiel, the son of Ocran;
\p 
\v 14 of Gad, Eliasaph, the son of Deuel;
\p 
\v 15 of Naphtali, Ahira, the son of Enan.
\p 
\v 16 These \em were\em* the noblest princes of the multitude, by their lineages, and kindreds, and the heads of the host\sls (s)\sls* of Israel, \sls (These \em were\em* the noblest leaders of the multitude, by their tribes, and kindreds, and the heads of the armies of Israel,)\sls*
\p 
\v 17 the which princes Moses and Aaron took, with all the multitude of the common people. \sls (which leaders Moses and Aaron took, along with all the multitude of the common people.)\sls*
\p 
\v 18 And they gathered \sls (them together)\sls* in the first day of the second month, and they told them, \sls (\em or and they totalled them\em*)\sls*, by kindreds, and houses, and families, and heads, and names of each by themselves, from the twentieth year and above, \sls (And they gathered them together on the first day of the second month, and they listed, \em or they registered\em*, them by their kindreds, and houses, and families, and heads, and their names, from twenty years of age and older,)\sls*
\p 
\v 19 as the Lord commanded to Moses, \sls (and so he numbered them there in the Sinai Desert)\sls*.
\p 
\v 20 And of Reuben, the first begotten of Israel, were numbered, in the desert of Sinai, by their generations, and families, and houses, and by the names of all the heads, all thing that is of male kind, from twenty years and above, of men going forth to battle, \sls (And so the sons of Reuben, the first-born of Israel, were listed by their generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, with the names of all who were twenty years of age and older, and all the men who could go forth to battle numbered)\sls*
\p 
\v 21 six and forty thousand and five hundred. \sls (forty-six thousand, five hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 22 Of the sons of Simeon, by their generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, were numbered, by the names and heads of all, all that is of male kind, from twenty years and above, of men going forth to battle, \sls (The sons of Simeon were listed by their generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, with the names of all who were twenty years of age and older, and all the men who could go forth to battle numbered)\sls*
\p 
\v 23 nine and fifty thousand and three hundred. \sls (fifty-nine thousand, three hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 24 Of the sons of Gad, by generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, were numbered, by the names of all, from twenty years and above, all men that went forth to battle, \sls (The sons of Gad were listed by their generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, with the names of all who were twenty years of age and older, and all the men who could go forth to battle numbered)\sls*
\p 
\v 25 five and forty thousand \sls (and)\sls* six hundred and fifty. \sls (forty-five thousand, six hundred and fifty.)\sls*
\p 
\v 26 Of the sons of Judah, by generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, by the names of all, from twenty years and above, all men that might go \add [forth]\add* to battles, \sls (The sons of Judah were listed by their generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, with the names of all who were twenty years of age and older, and all the men who could go forth to battle numbered)\sls*
\p 
\v 27 were numbered four and seventy thousand and six hundred. \sls (seventy-four thousand, six hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 28 Of the sons of Issachar, by their generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, by the names of all, from twenty years and above, all men that went forth to battles, \sls (The sons of Issachar were listed by their generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, with the names of all who were twenty years of age and older, and all the men who could go forth to battle numbered)\sls*
\p 
\v 29 were numbered four and fifty thousand and four hundred. \sls (fifty-four thousand, four hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 30 Of the sons of Zebulun, by generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, were numbered, by the names of all, from twenty years and above, all men that might go forth to battles, \sls (The sons of Zebulun were listed by their generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, with the names of all who were twenty years of age and older, and all the men who could go forth to battle numbered)\sls*
\p 
\v 31 seven and fifty thousand and four hundred. \sls (fifty-seven thousand, four hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 32 Of the sons of Joseph, of the sons of Ephraim, by generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, were numbered, by the names of all, from twenty years and above, all men that might go forth to battles, \sls (The sons of Joseph, those of the sons of Ephraim, were listed by their generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, with the names of all who were twenty years of age and older, and all the men who could go forth to battle numbered)\sls*
\p 
\v 33 forty thousand and five hundred. \sls (forty thousand, five hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 34 Forsooth of the sons of Manasseh, by their generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, were numbered, by the names of all, from twenty years and above, all men that might go forth to battles, \sls (And the sons of Manasseh were listed by their generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, with the names of all who were twenty years of age and older, and all the men who could go forth to battle numbered)\sls*
\p 
\v 35 two and thirty thousand and two hundred. \sls (thirty-two thousand, two hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 36 Of the sons of Benjamin, by generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, were numbered, by the names of all, from twenty years and above, all men that might go forth to battles, \sls (The sons of Benjamin were listed by their generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, with the names of all who were twenty years of age and older, and all the men who could go forth to battle numbered)\sls*
\p 
\v 37 five and thirty thousand and four hundred. \sls (thirty-five thousand, four hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 38 Of the sons of Dan, by generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, were numbered, by the names of all, from twenty years and above, all men that might go forth to battles, \sls (The sons of Dan were listed by their generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, with the names of all who were twenty years of age and older, and all the men who could go forth to battle numbered)\sls*
\p 
\v 39 two and sixty thousand and seven hundred. \sls (sixty-two thousand, seven hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 40 Of the sons of Asher, by generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, were numbered, by the names of all, from twenty years and above, all men that might go forth to battles, \sls (The sons of Asher were listed by their generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, with the names of all who were twenty years of age and older, and all the men who could go forth to battle numbered)\sls*
\p 
\v 41 forty thousand and a thousand and five hundred. \sls (forty-one thousand, five hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 42 Of the sons of Naphtali, by generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, were numbered, by the names of all, from twenty years and above, all men that might go forth to battles, \sls (The sons of Naphtali were listed by their generations, and families, and houses of their kindreds, with the names of all who were twenty years of age and older, and all the men who could go forth to battle numbered)\sls*
\p 
\v 43 three and fifty thousand and four
\p hundred. \sls (fifty-three thousand, four hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 44 These men it be, which Moses and Aaron and the twelve princes of Israel numbered, each by their houses and kindreds. \sls (These be the men, whom Moses and Aaron and the twelve leaders of Israel listed, \em or registered\em*, each by the house of his kindred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 45 And all men of the sons of Israel, by their houses, and families, from twenty years and above, that might go forth to battles, \sls (And all the men of the Israelites, by their houses, and families, from twenty years of age and older, who could go forth to battle,)\sls*
\p 
\v 46 were all together six hundred thousand and three thousand men, and five hundred and fifty. \sls (were altogether six hundred and three thousand, five hundred and fifty men.)\sls*
\p 
\v 47 Soothly the deacons\f + \fr 1:47 \ft Often in the Old Testament of the “\bk Wycliffe Bible\bk*”, where the “Later Version” has ‘deacon’ or ‘deacons’, the “Early Version” has ‘Levite’ or ‘Levites’.\f* in the lineage of their families were not numbered with them. \sls (But the Levites, in the tribe of their families, were not listed with them.)\sls*
\p 
\v 48 And the Lord spake to Moses, and said, \sls (For the Lord spoke to Moses, and said,)\sls*
\p 
\v 49 Do not thou number the lineage of Levi, neither set thou the sum of them with the sons of Israel; \sls (Do not thou list, \em or register\em*, the tribe of Levi, nor take thou the sum of them among the Israelites;)\sls*
\p 
\v 50 but thou shalt ordain them upon the tabernacle of \sls (the)\sls* witnessing, and upon all the vessels thereof, and \em upon\em* whatever thing pertaineth to \add [the]\add* ceremonies, \em either sacrifices\em*. They shall bear the tabernacle, and all the purtenances thereof, and they shall be in the service \em of it\em*, and they shall set \add [their]\add* tents by compass of the tabernacle \sls (or and they shall pitch their tents around the Tabernacle)\sls*.
\p 
\v 51 When men shall go forth, \em or be removed\em*, the deacons shall take down the tabernacle; when the tents shall be set \sls (up)\sls*, they shall set it up \sls (again)\sls*. Whoever of strangers nigheth \sls (to it)\sls*, he shall be slain \sls (or he shall be put to death)\sls*.
\p 
\v 52 Soothly the sons of Israel shall set tents, each man by \em his\em* companies, and his fellowships, and his host; \sls (And the other Israelites shall pitch their tents, each man in \em his\em* company, and his fellowship, and his army;)\sls*
\p 
\v 53 forsooth the deacons shall set their tents by compass of the tabernacle, lest indignation be made on the multitude of the sons of Israel; and they shall \sls (stand)\sls* watch in the keepings of the tabernacle of witnessing. \sls (but the Levites shall pitch their tents around the Tabernacle, lest my indignation come upon all the multitude of the Israelites; and they shall keep charge of the Tabernacle of the Witnessing.)\sls*
\p 
\v 54 Therefore the sons of Israel did by all things which the Lord commanded to Moses. \sls (And so the Israelites did all the things that the Lord commanded to Moses.)\sls*
\c 2
\cl CHAPTER 2
\p 
\v 1 And the Lord spake to Moses and to Aaron, and said,
\p 
\v 2 All men of the sons of Israel shall set tents by the companies, signs, and banners, and houses of their kindreds, by compass of the tabernacle of \add [the]\add* bond of peace. \sls (All the men of the Israelites shall pitch their tents by the companies, signs, and banners, and houses of their kindreds, around the Tabernacle of the Covenant, \em that is, the Tabernacle of the Witnessing\em*.)\sls*
\p 
\v 3 At the east Judah shall set tents, by the companies of his host; and Nahshon, the son of Amminadab, shall be prince of the sons of Judah; \sls (On the east side, the sons of Judah shall pitch their tents, by the companies of its army; and Nahshon, the son of Amminadab, shall be the leader of the sons of Judah;)\sls*
\p 
\v 4 and all the number of fighters of his kindred, four and seventy thousand and six hundred. \sls (and the number of all the fighters in his army, was seventy-four thousand and six hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 5 Men of the lineage of Issachar setted tents beside him, of which the prince was Nethaneel, the son of Zuar;
\p 
\v 6 and all the number of his fighters, four and fifty thousand and four hundred. \sls (and the number of all the fighters in his army, was fifty-four thousand and four hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 7 Eliab, the son of Helon, was prince of the lineage of Zebulun;
\p 
\v 8 all the host of fighters of his kindred, seven and fifty thousand and four hundred. \sls (and the number of all the fighters in his army, was fifty-seven thousand and four hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 9 \sls (So)\sls* All that were numbered in the tents of Judah, were an hundred thousand and fourscore thousand and six \sls (thousand)\sls* and four hundred; and they shall go out first by their companies.
\p 
\v 10 In the tents of the sons of Reuben, at the south coast, Elizur, the son of Shedeur, shall be prince; \sls (On the south side, the sons of Reuben shall pitch their tents, and Elizur, the son of Shedeur, shall be their leader;)\sls*
\p 
\v 11 and all the host of his fighters, that were numbered, six and forty thousand and five hundred. \sls (and the number of all the fighters in his army, was forty-six thousand and five hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 12 Men of the lineage of Simeon setted tents beside him, of which the prince was Shelumiel, the son of Zurishaddai;
\p 
\v 13 and all the host of his fighters, that were numbered, nine and fifty thousand and three hundred. \sls (and the number of all the fighters in his army, was fifty-nine thousand and three hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 14 Eliasaph, the son of Reuel, was prince in the lineage of Gad;
\p 
\v 15 and all the host of his fighters, that were numbered, five and forty thousand and six hundred and fifty. \sls (and the number of all the fighters in his army, was forty-five thousand and six hundred and fifty.)\sls*
\p 
\v 16 All that were numbered of the tents of Reuben \sls (or So all who were numbered in the tents of Reuben)\sls*, \sls (were)\sls* an hundred thousand and fifty thousand and one thousand and four hundred and fifty; they shall go forth in the second place by their companies.
\p 
\v 17 Soothly the tabernacle of witnessing shall be raised up by the offices of deacons, and by their companies; as it shall be raised up \em by them\em*, so it shall be taken down \em by them\em*; all they shall go forth by their places and orders. \sls (The Tabernacle of the Witnessing shall be raised up by the companies of the Levites; it shall be raised up \em by them\em*, and it shall be taken down \em by them\em*; and they all shall go forth in their proper place and order.)\sls*
\p 
\v 18 The tents of the sons of Ephraim shall be at the west coast, of which the prince was Elishama, the son of Ammihud; \sls (On the west side, the sons of Ephraim shall pitch their tents, and Elishama, the son of Amnmihud, shall be their leader;)\sls*
\p 
\v 19 and all the host of his fighters, that were numbered, forty thousand and five hundred. \sls (and the number of all the fighters in his army, was forty thousand and five hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 20 And with them was the lineage of the sons of Manasseh, of which the prince was Gamaliel, the son of Pedahzur;
\p 
\v 21 all the host of his fighters, that were numbered, \em were\em* two and thirty thousand and two hundred. \sls (and the number of all the fighters in his army, was thirty-two thousand and two hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 22 In the lineage of the sons of Benjamin, the prince was Abidan, the son of Gideoni;
\p 
\v 23 and all the host of his fighters, that were numbered, were five and thirty thousand and four hundred. \sls (and the number of all the fighters in his army, was thirty-five thousand and four hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 24 \sls (So)\sls* All men that were numbered in the tents of Ephraim were an hundred thousand and eight thousand and one hundred; they shall go forth in the third \em place\em* by their companies.
\p 
\v 25 At the north coast the sons of Dan setted tents, of which the prince was Ahiezer, the son of Ammishaddai; \sls (And on the north side, the sons of Dan shall pitch their tents, and Ahiezer, the son of Ammishaddai, shall be their leader;)\sls*
\p 
\v 26 all the host of his fighters, that were numbered, \em were\em* two and sixty thousand and seven hundred. \sls (and the number of all the fighters in his army, was sixty-two thousand and seven hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 27 And men of the lineage of Asher setted tents beside him, of which the prince was Pagiel, the son of Ocran;
\p 
\v 28 and all the host of his fighters, that were numbered, were one and forty thousand and five hundred. \sls (and the number of all the fighters in his army, was forty-one thousand and five hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 29 Of the lineage of the sons of Naphtali, the prince was Ahira, the son of Enan; \sls (In the tribe of the sons of Naphtali, the leader was Ahira, the son of Enan;)\sls*
\p 
\v 30 and all the host of his fighters, \sls (that were numbered)\sls*, were three and fifty thousand and four hundred. \sls (and the number of all the fighters in his army, was fifty-three thousand and four hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 31 \sls (So)\sls* All that were numbered in the tents of Dan were an hundred thousand and seven \sls (thousand)\sls* and fifty thousand and six hundred; they shall go forth the last.
\p 
\v 32 This is the number of the sons of Israel, by the houses of their kindreds, and by companies of the host parted, six hundred thousand and three thousand five hundred and fifty. \sls (And so the number of the Israelites, by the houses of their kindreds, and by the companies of each of their separate armies, was six hundred thousand and three thousand and five hundred and fifty.)\sls*
\p 
\v 33 Soothly the deacons were not numbered among the sons of Israel; for God commanded so to Moses. \sls (But the Levites were not listed, \em or were not registered\em*, among the Israelites; for God had so commanded to Moses.)\sls*
\p 
\v 34 And the sons of Israel did by all things which the Lord commanded; they setted tents by their companies, and they went forth by the families, and houses of their fathers. \sls (And the Israelites did all the things that the Lord commanded; they pitched their tents by their companies, and they went forth by their families, and the houses of their fathers.)\sls*
\c 3
\cl CHAPTER 3
\p 
\v 1 These be the generations of Aaron and of Moses, in the day in which the Lord spake to Moses, in the hill of Sinai. \sls (These be the generations of Aaron and of Moses, on the day in which the Lord spoke to Moses, on Mount Sinai.)\sls*
\p 
\v 2 And these be the names of the sons of Aaron; his first engendered, Nadab, \sls (or Nadab, his first-born)\sls*; afterward, Abihu, and Eleazar, and Ithamar;
\p 
\v 3 these be the names of Aaron’s sons, \sls (the)\sls* priests, that were anointed, and whose hands were \add [ful]\add* filled and hallowed, that they should be set in priesthood. \sls (these be the names of Aaron’s sons, the priests, who were anointed, and consecrated, so that they could be installed, \em or ordained\em*, in the priesthood.)\sls*
\p 
\v 4 Nadab and Abihu \add [died]\add*, when they offered alien fire in the sight of the Lord, in the desert of Sinai, \sls (and they)\sls* were dead without free children; and Eleazar and Ithamar were set in priesthood before Aaron their father. \sls (But then Nadab and Abihu were killed, when they offered unholy fire before the Lord, in the Sinai Desert, and they died before having any children; and so Eleazar and Ithamar were ordained in the priesthood in the sight of their father Aaron.)\sls*
\p 
\v 5 And the Lord spake to Moses, saying,
\p 
\v 6 Present thou the lineage of Levi, and make it to stand in the sight of Aaron, the priest, that they minister to him; \sls (Present thou the tribe of Levi, and make them to stand before Aaron, the priest, to serve him;)\sls*
\p 
\v 7 and \sls (to stand)\sls* watch, and that they keep whatever thing pertaineth to the religion of the multitude, before the tabernacle of witnessing; \sls (and to keep charge, and to do whatever thing pertaineth to the service of the multitude, in the Tabernacle of the Witnessing;)\sls*
\p 
\v 8 and that they keep \sls (charge of)\sls* the vessels of the tabernacle, and serve in the service of it.
\p 
\v 9 And thou shalt give by free gift the Levites to Aaron and to his sons, to whom they be given \sls (out)\sls* of the sons of Israel. \sls (And thou shalt give the Levites as a gift to Aaron and his sons, to whom they be given from all the Israelites.)\sls*
\p 
\v 10 Soothly thou shalt ordain Aaron and his sons on the religion of priesthood; a stranger that nigheth for to minister, shall die. \sls (And thou shalt ordain Aaron and his sons to serve in the priesthood; a stranger who cometh near to try to minister, shall be put to death.)\sls*
\p 
\v 11 And the Lord spake to Moses, saying,
\p 
\v 12 I have taken the Levites \sls (out)\sls* of the sons of Israel for each first engendered \sls (male)\sls* thing that openeth the womb in the sons of Israel; and the Levites shall be mine,
\p 
\v 13 for each first engendered \sls (male)\sls* thing is mine; since \em the time\em* I smote the first engendered \sls (male)\sls* thing in the land of Egypt, I have hallowed to me whatever \sls (male)\sls* thing is born first in Israel \sls (or I have consecrated to myself whatever male is first-born in Israel)\sls*; from man unto beast they be mine; I am the Lord.
\p 
\v 14 And the Lord spake to Moses in the desert of Sinai, and said,
\p 
\v 15 Number thou the sons of Levi by their fathers’ houses, and by their families, each male from one month and above \sls (or every male one month of age and older)\sls*.
\p 
\v 16 \add [And]\add* Moses numbered \em them\em*, as the Lord commanded.
\p 
\v 17 And the sons of Levi were found, by their names, Gershon, and Kohath, and Merari;
\p 
\v 18 the sons of Gershon \em were\em* Libni, and Shimei;
\p 
\v 19 the sons of Kohath \em were\em* Amram, and Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel;
\p 
\v 20 and the sons of Merari \em were\em* Mahli, and Mushi.
\p 
\v 21 Of Gershon were two families, \sls (they)\sls* of Libni, and \sls (they)\sls* of Shimei;
\p 
\v 22 of which the people of male kind was numbered, from one month and above, seven thousand and five hundred. \sls (of whom the number of the males, who were one month of age and older, was seven thousand and five hundred.)\sls*
\p 
\v 23 These shall set tents behind the tabernacle at the west part, \sls (They shall pitch their tents behind the Tabernacle, on the west side,)\sls*
\p 
\v 24 under the prince Eliasaph, the son of Lael. \sls (and their leader shall be Eliasaph, the son of Lael.)\sls*
\p 
\v 25 And they shall have the keepings in the tabernacle of \add [the]\add* bond of peace, the tabernacle itself, and the covering thereof, \sls (and)\sls* the tent that is drawn before the gates of the covering of the witnessing of the bond of peace; \sls (And they shall keep charge of the Tabernacle of the Covenant, that is, the Tabernacle itself, and its coverings, and the curtain which is hung at the entrance to the Tabernacle of the Covenant;)\sls*
\p 
\v 26 and the curtains of the great entry, also the tent that is hanged in the entering of the great entry of the tabernacle, and whatever thing pertaineth to the use of the altar, the cords of the tabernacle, and to all the service thereof. \sls (and the curtains for the courtyard all around the Tabernacle, and the curtain that is hung at the entrance to the courtyard, and whatever pertaineth to the use of the altar, and all the other things in the service thereof.)\sls*
\p 
\v 27 The kindred of Kohath shall have the peoples of Amram, and of Izhar, and of Hebron, and of Uzziel; these be the families of Kohathites,
\p 
\v 28 numbered by their names, all of male kind, from one month and above, eight thousand and six hundred. They shall have the keepings of the saintuary, \sls (and the number of all the males, from one month of age and older, was eight thousand and six hundred. They shall keep charge of the holy things of the sanctuary,)\sls*
\p 
\v 29 and they shall set their tents at the south coast \em thereof\em*; \sls (and they shall pitch their tents on \em its\em* south side;)\sls*
\p 
\v 30 and the prince of them shall be Elizaphan, the son of Uzziel. \sls (and their leader shall be Elizaphan, the son of Uzziel.)\sls*
\p 
\v 31 And they shall keep \sls (charge of)\sls* the ark, and the table, and the candlestick, the altars, and the vessels of the saintuary in which it is served, and the veil, and all such manner purtenance. \sls (And they shall keep charge of the Ark, \em that is, the Box containing the tablets of the Law\em*, and the table, and the lampstand, and the altars, and the vessels of the sanctuary with which they shall serve, \em or they shall minister\em*, and the Veil, and all the other things in the service thereof.)\sls*
\p 
\v 32 Soothly the prince of princes of Levites shall be Eleazar, the son of Aaron, the priest; and he shall be upon the keepers of the keeping of the saintuary. \sls (And the leader of the leaders of the Levites shall be Eleazar, the son of Aaron, the priest; and he shall be over those in charge of the sanctuary.)\sls*
\p 
\v 33 And soothly of Merari shall be the peoples of Mahli, and of Mushi,
\p 
\v 34 numbered by their names, all the male kind, from one month and above, six thousand and two hundred; \sls (and the number of all the males, from one month of age and older, was six thousand and two hundred;)\sls*
\p 
\v 35 the prince of them \em shall be\em* Zuriel, the son of Abihail; they shall set their tents in the north coast. \sls (their leader \em shall be\em* Zuriel, the son of Abihail; and they shall pitch their tents on the north side of the Tabernacle.)\sls*
\p 
\v 36 And under the keeping of them shall be the tables of the tabernacle, and the bars, and the pillars, and the foundaments of those, and all things that pertain to such adorning, \sls (And the sons of Merari shall be in charge of the tables of the Tabernacle, and the bars, and the pillars, and their foundations, \em or their bases\em*, and all the things in the service thereof,)\sls*
\p 
\v 37 and the pillars of the great entry by compass \sls (or and the pillars all around the courtyard)\sls*, with their bases, and the stakes with \em their\em* cords.
\p 
\v 38 Forsooth Moses, and Aaron with his sons, shall set \em their\em* tents before the tabernacle of \add [the]\add* bond of peace, that is, at the east coast, and shall have the keeping of the saintuary, in the midst of the sons of Israel; whatever alien nigheth \em thereto\em*, he shall die. \sls (And Moses, and Aaron with his sons, shall pitch \em their\em* tents in front of the Tabernacle of the Covenant, that is, on the east side, and they shall be in charge of the sanctuary, on behalf of the Israelites; and any stranger who cometh near \em to it\em*, shall be put to death.)\sls*
\p 
\v 39 All the Levites, which Moses and Aaron numbered, by the commandment of the Lord, by their families, in male kind, from one month and above, were two and twenty thousand. \sls (And the number of all the Levites, whom Moses and Aaron listed, \em or registered\em*, by the Lord’s command, by their families, all the males from one month of age and older, was twenty-two thousand.)\sls*
\p 
\v 40 And the Lord said to Moses, Number thou the first begotten of male kind of the sons of Israel, from one month and above \sls (or from one month of age and older)\sls*; and thou shalt have the sum, \em or the number\em*, of them;
\p 
\v 41 and thou shalt take the Levites to me for all the first begotten of the sons of Israel; I am the Lord; and \em thou shalt take\em* their beasts \sls (to me)\sls* for all the first begotten of the sons of Israel. \sls (and thou shalt give me the Levites in place of all the first-born sons of the Israelites; I am the Lord; and \em thou shalt give\em* me the beasts of the Levites, in place of all the first-born male beasts of the Israelites.)\sls*
\p 
\v 42 And as the Lord commanded, Moses numbered the first begotten \sls (male)\sls* children of the sons of Israel;
\p 
\v 43 and the males were by their names, from one month and above, two and twenty thousand two hundred and seventy and three. \sls (and the number of the males, listed by their names, from one month of age and older, was twenty-two thousand and two hundred and seventy-three.)\sls*
\p 
\v 44 And the Lord spake to Moses, and said,
\p 
\v 45 Take thou the Levites for the first begotten of the sons of Israel, and take the beasts of the Levites for the beasts of them, and the Levites shall be mine; I am the Lord. \sls (Now give me the Levites in place of all the first-born sons of the Israelites, and the beasts of the Levites in place of the first-born male beasts of the Israelites, and so the Levites shall be mine; I am the Lord.)\sls*
\p 
\v 46 Forsooth in the price of two hundred and seventy and three \em persons\em*, that pass the number of the Levites, of the first begotten \sls (sons)\sls* of the sons of Israel, \sls (And as payment to buy back the two hundred and seventy-three \em persons\em*, of the first-born sons of the Israelites, who surpass the number of the Levites,)\sls*
\p 
\v 47 thou shalt take five shekels by each head, at the measure of the saintuary, \sls (or thou shalt take five shekels for each one, by the measure of the sanctuary)\sls*; a shekel hath twenty halfpence;
\p 
\v 48 and thou shalt give the money to Aaron and to his sons, the price of them that be \em numbered\em* above \sls (the number of the Levites)\sls*. \sls (and thou shalt give this money to Aaron and to his sons, as payment for those who be \em listed, or registered\em*, above the number of the Levites.)\sls*
\p 
\v 49 Therefore Moses took the money of them that were \em numbered\em* above, and which they had again-bought of the Levites, \sls (And so Moses took the money for the first-born sons of the Israelites, who surpassed the number of the Levites, and so had to be bought back, \em or ransomed, or redeemed\em*,)\sls*
\p 
\v 50 for the first begotten \sls (sons)\sls* of the sons of Israel, a thousand three hundred and sixty and five of shekels, by the weight of the saintuary; \sls (in all, a thousand and three hundred and sixty-five shekels, by the measure of the sanctuary;)\sls*
\p 
\v 51 and he gave that \em money\em* to Aaron and to his sons, by the word that the Lord commanded to him.
\c 4
\cl CHAPTER 4
\p 
\v 1 And the Lord spake to Moses and to Aaron, and said,
\p 
\v 2 Take thou the sum, \em or the number\em*, of the sons of Kohath, from the midst of \sls (the)\sls* Levites, by their houses and families,
\p 
\v 3 from the thirtieth year and above unto the fiftieth year, of all that enter, that they stand and minister in the tabernacle of the bond of peace. \sls (from thirty years of age up to fifty years old, of all who enter to serve in the Tabernacle of the Covenant.)\sls*
\p 
\v 4 This is the religion of the sons of Kohath; Aaron and his sons shall enter into the tabernacle of the bond of peace, and into the holy of holy things, \sls (This is the service of the sons of Kohath; Aaron and his sons shall enter into the Tabernacle of the Covenant, and into the Most Holy Place, \em or the Holy of Holies\em*,)\sls*
\p 
\v 5 when the tents shall be moved; and they shall do down the veil that hangeth before the gates, and they shall wrap in it the ark of witnessing; \sls (when the tents shall be moved; and they shall take down the Veil that hangeth before the Ark, and they shall wrap the Ark of the Witnessing, \em that is, the Box containing the tablets of the Law\em*, in it;)\sls*
\p 
\v 6 and they shall cover \em it\em* again with a veil of jacinthine skins, and they shall stretch forth above \sls (that)\sls* a mantle all of jacinth, and they shall lead in \add [the]\add* bearing staves. \sls (and they shall wrap \em it\em* with a leather cover, and put a blue mantle over that, and then put in the carrying bars.)\sls*
\p 
\v 7 Also they shall wrap the board of proposition, \em that is, \sls (of)\sls* setting forth\em*, in a mantle of jacinth, and they shall put therewith \add [the]\add* censers, and spoons of gold, little cups, and great cups to flowing sacrifices to be shed \sls (out)\sls*; loaves shall ever\add [more]\add* be in the board. \sls (And they shall wrap the table of proposition, \em that is, the table of setting forth\em*, in a blue mantle, and they shall put the censers, and the gold saucers, and the little cups, and the great cups for the wine offerings upon it; and loaves shall be on the table forevermore.)\sls*
\p 
\v 8 And they shall stretch forth thereabove a red mantle, which they shall cover again with a covering of jacinthine skins, and they shall lead in the bearing staves. \sls (And they shall spread a red mantle over them, and put a leather cover over that, and then put in the carrying bars.)\sls*
\p 
\v 9 They shall take also a mantle of jacinth with which they shall cover the candlestick, with his lanterns, and tongs, and snuffers, and all the oil vessels that be needful to the lanterns to be ordained; \sls (And they shall take a blue mantle with which they shall cover the lampstand, with its lanterns, and tongs, and snuffers, and all the oil vessels that be needed for the lanterns to be lit;)\sls*
\p 
\v 10 and upon all these things they shall put a covering of jacinthine skins, and they shall bring, \em or lead\em*, in the bearing staves. \sls (and they shall wrap all these things in a leather cover, and then put it on a carrying bar, \em or a carrying pole\em*.)\sls*
\p 
\v 11 Also they shall wrap the golden altar in a cloth of jacinth; and they shall stretch forth above it a covering of jacinthine skins, and they shall lead in \add [the]\add* bearing staves. \sls (And they shall wrap the gold altar in a blue mantle; and they shall wrap that in a leather cover, and then put in the carrying bars.)\sls*
\p 
\v 12 They shall wrap in a mantle of jacinth all the vessels in which it is ministered in the saintuary, and they shall stretch forth above \em it\em* a covering of jacinthine skins, and they shall lead in the bearing staves. \sls (And they shall wrap all the vessels with which they minister in the sanctuary in a blue mantle, and they shall wrap \em that\em* in a leather cover, and then put \em it\em* on a carrying bar, \em or a carrying pole\em*.)\sls*
\p 
\v 13 But also they shall cleanse the altar from \sls (all)\sls* ashes, and \sls (then)\sls* they shall wrap it in a cloth of purple.
\p 
\v 14 And they shall put with it all the vessels which they use in the service thereof, that is, the resets of fire, the tongs, and fleshhooks, and other hooks, and the censers, or the pans of coals; they shall cover all the vessels of the altar \sls (al)\sls*together in a veil of jacinthine skins, and they shall lead in the bearing staves. \sls (And they shall put on the altar all the vessels which they use in its service, that is, the fire receptacles, the tongs, and flesh-hooks, and other hooks, and the censers, or the pans, for the coal; and they shall cover all the vessels of the altar with a leather cover, and then put in the carrying bars.)\sls*
\p 
\v 15 And when Aaron and his sons have wrapped the saintuary, and all \add [the]\add* vessels thereof, in the moving of tents, then the sons of Kohath shall enter, that they bear the things wrapped, and touch not the vessels of the saintuary, lest they die. These be the burdens of the sons of Kohath in the tabernacle of \add [the]\add* bond of peace, \sls (And when Aaron and his sons have wrapped up the sanctuary, and all its vessels, in the moving of the tents, then the sons of Kohath shall enter to carry the things that be wrapped up, but they must not touch the sanctuary vessels, or they shall die, or for if they touch them, then they must be put to death. These be the loads for the sons of Kohath in the Tabernacle of the Covenant.)\sls*
\p 
\v 16 on which Eleazar, the son of Aaron, \sls (the)\sls* priest, shall be; to whose care the oil pertaineth \sls (with which)\sls* to ordain \sls (the)\sls* lanterns, and the incense which is made by craft, and the sacrifice which is offered ever\add [more]\add*, \em that is, in each day\em*, and the oil of anointing, and whatever thing pertaineth to the adorning of the tabernacle, and of all vessels that be in the saintuary. \sls (And Eleazar, the son of Aaron, the priest, shall be in charge of the oil to fuel the lanterns, and the incense which is made by craft, and the offering which is offered forevermore, \em that is, on each day\em*, and the oil of anointing, for he is in charge of whatever pertaineth to the service of the Tabernacle, and of all the vessels that be in the sanctuary.)\sls*
\p 
\v 17 And the Lord spake to Moses and to Aaron, and said,
\p 
\v 18 Do not ye lose, \em or destroy\em*, the people of Kohath from the midst of the Levites; \sls (Do not ye allow the people of Kohath to be done away from the midst of the Levites;)\sls*
\p 
\v 19 but do ye this thing to them, that they live, and die not, if they touch the holy of holy things. Aaron and his sons shall enter, and they shall dispose the works of all \em the sons of Kohath\em*, and they shall part \sls (to each)\sls* what who oughteth to bear. \sls (but do ye this thing for them, so that they shall live, and not die, when they approach the most holy things. Aaron and his sons shall enter, and they shall direct the works of all \em the sons of Kohath\em*, and they shall assign to each what he ought to carry.)\sls*
\p 
\v 20 Other men see not by any curiosity those things that be in the saintuary, before that those be wrapped; else they shall die. \sls (And do not let other people who be curious see those things that be in the sanctuary, before that they be wrapped up; for if they do, then they shall die or then they must be put to death.)\sls*
\p 
\v 21 And the Lord spake to Moses, and said,
\p 
\v 22 Take thou the sum, \em or the number\em*, also of the sons of Gershon, by their houses, and families, and kindreds; \sls (Take thou also the sum, \em or the number\em*, of the sons of Gershon, by their houses, and families, and kindreds;)\sls*
\p 
\v 23 number thou \em them\em* from thirty years and above unto fifty years, all that enter and serve in the tabernacle of the bond of peace. \sls (make thou a list of \em them\em* from thirty years of age up to fifty years old, all who enter to serve in the Tabernacle of the Covenant.)\sls*
\p 
\v 24 This is the office of the sons of Gershonites, \sls (This is the service of the sons of the Gershonites,)\sls*
\p 
\v 25 that they bear the curtains of the tabernacle, and the roof, \em or covering\em*, of the bond of peace, another covering, and the veil of jacinth that shall be above all things, and the tent that hangeth in the entry of the tabernacle of the bond of peace; \sls (that they carry the curtains of the Tabernacle, and the Tent of the Tabernacle of the Covenant, another cover, the leather cover that shall be on top of it, and the curtain that hangeth in the entrance to the Tabernacle of the Covenant;)\sls*
\p 
\v 26 and the curtains of the great entry, and the veil in the entry, that is before the tabernacle \sls (by compass)\sls*. \sls (and the curtains of the courtyard, that is all around the Tabernacle, and the curtain at the entrance to the courtyard.)\sls*
\p 
\v 27 When Aaron commandeth and his sons, the sons of Gershon shall bear all things that pertain to the altar, the cords, and the vessels, \em or instruments\em*, of their service; and all \em they\em* shall know, to what charge they ought to be bound. \sls (And when Aaron and his sons command, the sons of Gershon shall carry all the things that pertain to the altar, and the cords, and the vessels, \em or the instruments\em*, of their service; and \em they\em* all shall know, what each of them ought to carry.)\sls*
\p 
\v 28 This is the office of the families of Gershonites, in the tabernacle of \add [the]\add* bond of peace, \sls (or This is the service of the Gershonite families in the Tabernacle of the Covenant)\sls*; and they shall be under the hand of Ithamar, the son of Aaron, \add [the]\add* priest.
\p 
\v 29 Also thou shalt number the sons of Merari, by the families and houses of their fathers,
\p 
\v 30 from thirty years and above unto fifty years, all that enter to the office of their service, and to the adorning of the bond of peace of witnessing. \sls (from thirty years of age up to fifty years old, all who enter to serve in the Tabernacle of the Covenant, \em that is, in the Tabernacle of the Witnessing\em*.)\sls*
\p 
\v 31 These be their charges; they shall bear the tables of the tabernacle, and the bars thereof, the pillars, and their foundaments \sls (or and their foundations, \em or their bases\em*)\sls*;
\p 
\v 32 also the pillars of the great entry by compass, with their foundaments, and their stakes, and their cords, \sls (or and the pillars all around the courtyard, with their bases, and their stakes, and their cords)\sls*; and they shall take all the instruments and the purtenance of \em the tabernacle\em*, by number, and so they shall bear \em them\em*.
\p 
\v 33 This is the office of the family of Merarites, and the service in the tabernacle of the bond of peace, \sls (or These be the duties of the Merarite family, in their service in the Tabernacle of the Covenant)\sls*; and they shall be under the hand of Ithamar, the son of Aaron, the priest.
\p 
\v 34 Therefore Moses and Aaron and the princes of the synagogue, numbered the sons of Kohath, by the kindreds, and houses of their fathers, \sls (And so Moses and Aaron and the leaders of the congregation, listed, \em or registered\em*, the Kohathites, by the kindreds, and houses of their fathers,)\sls*
\p 
\v 35 from thirty years and above unto the fiftieth year, all that enter to the service of the tabernacle of \add [the]\add* bond of peace; \sls (from thirty years of age up to fifty years old, all who entered to serve in the Tabernacle of the Covenant;)\sls*
\p 
\v 36 and they were found \sls (to be)\sls* two thousand \sls (and)\sls* seven hundred and fifty.
\p 
\v 37 This is the number of the people of Kohath, which entereth into the tabernacle of \add [the]\add* bond of peace; Moses and Aaron numbered these, by the word of the Lord, by the hand of Moses. \sls (This is the number of the people of Kohath, who served in the Tabernacle of the Covenant; Moses and Aaron listed them, obeying the word of the Lord, spoken by Moses.)\sls*
\p 
\v 38 And the sons of Gershon were numbered, by the kindreds and houses of their fathers,
\p 
\v 39 from thirty years and above unto fifty years, all that enter that they serve in the tabernacle of \add [the]\add* bond of peace; \sls (from thirty years of age up to fifty years old, all who entered to serve in the Tabernacle of the Covenant;)\sls*
\p 
\v 40 and they were found \sls (to be)\sls* two thousand \sls (and)\sls* six hundred and thirty.
\p 
\v 41 This is the people of Gershonites, that Moses and Aaron numbered, by the kindreds and houses, by the word of the Lord.
\p 
\v 42 And the sons of Merari were numbered, by the kindreds, and houses of their fathers,
\p 
\v 43 from thirty years and above unto fifty years, all that enter to fulfill the customs, \em or the services\em*, of the tabernacle of the bond of peace; \sls (from thirty years of age up to fifty years old, all who entered to serve in the Tabernacle of the Covenant;)\sls*
\p 
\v 44 and they were found \sls (to be)\sls* three thousand and two hundred.
\p 
\v 45 This is the number of the sons of Merari, which Moses and Aaron numbered, by the commandment of the Lord, by the hand of Moses. \sls (This is the number of the Merarites, whom Moses and Aaron listed, \em or registered\em*, by the Lord’s command, spoken by Moses.)\sls*
\p 
\v 46 All that were numbered of the Levites, and which Moses and Aaron and the princes of Israel made to be numbered, by the kindreds, and houses of their fathers,
\p 
\v 47 from thirty years and above unto fifty years, and entered to the service of the tabernacle, and to bear the charges thereof, \sls (from thirty years of age up to fifty years old, and entered to serve in the Tabernacle, and to carry its loads,)\sls*
\p 
\v 48 were \sls (al)\sls*together eight thousand \sls (and)\sls* five hundred and fourscore.
\p 
\v 49 By the word of the Lord Moses numbered them, each man by his office and his charges \sls (or each one according to his service and his loads)\sls*, as the Lord commanded to him.
\c 5
\cl CHAPTER 5
\p 
\v 1 And the Lord spake to Moses, and said,
\p 
\v 2 Command thou to the sons of Israel, that they cast out of the tents each leprous man, and that floweth out the seed, and that is defouled upon a dead body; \sls (Command thou to the Israelites, that they throw out of the tents, \em that is, out of the camp\em*, any person who is leprous, and he who floweth out the seed, and anyone who is defiled by contact with a dead body;)\sls*
\p 
\v 3 cast ye out of the tents, as well a male as a female, lest they defoul those, when they dwell with you. \sls (throw ye out of the camp, a female as well as a male, lest they defile all the tents, where I live among you.)\sls*
\p 
\v 4 And the sons of Israel did so \sls (or And the Israelites did so)\sls*; and they putted them out of the tents, as the Lord spake to Moses.
\p 
\v 5 And the Lord spake to Moses, and said,
\p 
\v 6 Speak thou to the sons of Israel \sls (or Say thou to the Israelites)\sls*, When a man either a woman hath done any of all \sls (of)\sls* the sins that be wont to fall to men, and have broken by negligence the behest of the Lord, and have trespassed,
\p 
\v 7 they shall acknowledge their sin, and they shall yield that head, \em or debt\em*, and \sls (add)\sls* the fifth part above \sls (it)\sls*, \sls (and give it)\sls* to him against whom they \sls (have)\sls* sinned.
\p 
\v 8 But if none there is that shall receive \em that\em*, they shall give it to the Lord, and it shall be the priest’s \em part\em*, besides the ram that is offered for cleansing, that it be a quemeful sacrifice. \sls (But if there is no one who can receive \em that payment\em*, then they shall give it to the Lord, and it shall be the priest’s \em portion\em*, besides the ram for making amends, which is offered to make amends for them.)\sls*
\p 
\v 9 Also all the first fruits, which the sons of Israel offer \sls (or which the Israelites offer)\sls*, pertain to the priest;
\p 
\v 10 and whatever thing is offered of each man in the saintuary, which a man hallowed, and gave to the hands of the priest, it shall be the priest’s part. \sls (and whatever thing is offered by anyone in the sanctuary, which a person hath dedicated, and put into the hands of the priest, it shall be the priest’s portion.)\sls*
\p 
\v 11 And the Lord spake to Moses, and said,
\p 
\v 12 Speak thou to the sons of Israel \sls (or Say thou to the Israelites)\sls*, and thou shalt say to them, If a man’s wife hath erred, and hath despised her husband,
\p 
\v 13 and hath slept with another man, and the husband may not take, \em either prove\em* this, but the adultery is hid, and may not be proved by witnesses, for she is not found in lechery; \sls (and hath slept with another man, but her husband cannot prove it, for the adultery is hidden, \em or is done in secret\em*, and so cannot be proved by witnesses, for she was not found in lechery;)\sls*
\p 
\v 14 \sls (or)\sls* if the spirit of jealousy stirreth the husband against his wife, which is either defouled, either she is impeached by false suspicion, \sls (or if the spirit of jealousy stirreth a husband against his wife, and she is either truly defiled, or is impeached by false suspicion,)\sls*
\p 
\v 15 the man shall bring her to the priest, and he shall offer an offering for her, the tenth part of a measure called \sls (a)\sls* saton of barley meal; he shall not pour oil thereupon, neither he shall put incense \em thereto\em*, for it is the sacrifice of jealousy, and an offering inquiring \sls (about)\sls* adultery. \sls (the husband shall bring her to the priest, and he shall offer an offering for her, the tenth of a measure called a seah of barley meal, \em that is, the tenth of an ephah\em*; he shall not pour oil on it, nor shall he put incense \em on it\em*, for it is an offering for jealousy, and an offering to inquire about adultery.)\sls*
\p 
\v 16 Therefore the priest shall offer her, and shall set \em her\em* before the Lord; \sls (And so the priest shall bring her forth, and shall put \em her\em* before the Lord;)\sls*
\p 
\v 17 and he shall take holy water in an earthen vessel, and he shall put into it a little earth of the pavement of the tabernacle. \sls (and he shall pour some holy water into an earthen, \em or a clay\em*, vessel, and he shall put into it a little dust, \em or a little dirt\em*, from the floor of the Tabernacle, \em to make the water bitter\em*.)\sls*
\p 
\v 18 And when the woman standeth in the sight of the Lord, the priest shall uncover her head, and he shall put upon her hands the sacrifice of remembering, and the offering of jealousy. Soothly he shall hold \sls (in his hand)\sls* the most bitter waters, in which he hath gathered together curses with cursing. \sls (And when the woman standeth before the Lord, the priest shall uncover her head, and he shall put in her hands the offering of remembrance, which is the offering for jealousy. And he shall hold in his hand this most bitter water, into which he shall gather together curses.)\sls*
\p 
\v 19 And he shall conjure her, and say, If an alien man slept not with thee, and if thou art not defouled in forsaking the bed of thine husband, these bitter waters shall not harm thee, into which I have gathered together curses; \sls (And he shall adjure her, and say, If thou hath not slept with a stranger, and if thou art not defiled by forsaking thy husband’s bed, then this most bitter water, into which I shall gather together curses, shall not harm thee;)\sls*
\p 
\v 20 else if thou bowedest away from thine husband, and art defouled, and hast lain with another man, \sls (but if thou hast turned away from thy husband, and art defiled, and hast lain with another man,)\sls*
\p 
\v 21 thou shalt be subject to these cursings; the Lord give thee into cursing, and into ensample of all men in his people; \em the Lord\em* make thine hip to wax rotten, and thy womb \sls (to)\sls* swell, and be it broken; \sls (then thou shalt be subject to these curses; yea, let the Lord make thee a curse, and an example to all among his people; \em and may the Lord\em* make thy hip to grow rotten, and thy womb to swell, and let it be broken;)\sls*
\p 
\v 22 \em \sls ( yea, let)\sls* these\em* cursed waters enter into thy womb, and while thy womb swelleth, thine hip wax rotten. And the woman shall answer, Amen! amen!
\p 
\v 23 And the priest shall write these curses in a little book, and he shall do away those curses with the bitterest waters \sls (or and then he shall wash them off into this most bitter water)\sls*,
\p 
\v 24 into which he gathered \sls (those)\sls* curses, and he shall give to her \em the waters\em* to drink. And when she hath drunk those waters, \sls (into which he shall gather together these curses, and then he shall give her \em this water\em* to drink. And when she hath drunk the water,)\sls*
\p 
\v 25 the priest shall take \sls (out)\sls* of her hand the sacrifice of jealousy \sls (or the priest shall take from her hand the offering for jealousy)\sls*, and he shall raise it \add [up]\add* before the Lord, and he shall put it on the altar;
\p 
\v 26 so only that he take before an handful of that sacrifice that is offered, and burn it upon the altar, and so give \sls (for to)\sls* drink to the woman the most bitter waters. \sls (so only that first he take a handful of the offering that is offered, and burn it on the altar, and then afterward give the woman this most bitter water to drink.)\sls*
\p 
\v 27 And when she hath drunk those waters, if she is defouled, and is guilty of adultery, for her husband is despised \em of her\em*\sls (or for her husband was despised \em by her\em*)\sls*, the waters of cursing shall pass through her, and while her womb is swollen, her hip shall wax rotten, and the woman shall be into cursing and into ensample to all the people.
\p 
\v 28 That if she is not defouled, she shall be harmless, and shall bring forth free children. \sls (But if she is not defiled, she shall be without harm, and shall bring forth children.)\sls*
\p 
\v 29 This is the law of jealousy, if a woman boweth away from her husband, and is defouled, \sls (This is the law of jealousy, when a woman turneth away from her husband, and is defiled,)\sls*
\p 
\v 30 and the husband is stirred with the spirit of jealousy, and bringeth her into the sight of the Lord, and the priest doeth to her by all things that be written \sls (here)\sls*, \sls (or when her husband is stirred with the spirit of jealousy, \em or of suspicion\em*, and he bringeth her before the Lord, and the priest doeth to her by all the things that be written here;)\sls*
\p 
\v 31 the husband shall be without sin, and she shall receive her wickedness. \sls (then the husband shall be without sin, and she, if guilty, shall bear her wickedness.)\sls*
\c 6
\cl CHAPTER 6
\p 
\v 1 And the Lord spake to Moses, and said,
\p 
\v 2 Speak thou to the sons of Israel, and thou shalt say to them, When a man either a woman maketh a vow, that they be hallowed, and they will hallow themselves to the Lord, \sls (Say thou to the Israelites, When a man or a woman maketh a vow, that they will become a Nazarite, and they will consecrate, \em or will dedicate\em*, themselves to the Lord,)\sls*
\p 
\v 3 they shall abstain from wine, and from all thing that may make drunken; they shall not drink vinegar of wine, and of anything able to make drunken, and whatever thing is pressed out of the grape; they shall not eat fresh grapes and dry, \sls (they shall abstain from wine, and from all things that can make them drunk; they shall not drink wine vinegar, or any other thing that is able to make them drunk, or whatever is pressed out of the grape; they shall not eat fresh grapes, or dried grapes,)\sls*
\p 
\v 4 all \add [the]\add* days in which they be hallowed by a vow to the Lord; they shall not eat whatever thing may be of the vinery, from the rind till to the little grains that be in the midst of the grape.
\p 
\v 5 All the time of his separating, \em or of his avow holding\em*, a razor shall not pass upon his head, unto the day\sls (s)\sls* be fulfilled in which he is hallowed to the Lord; he shall be holy, and the hair of his head shall wax. \sls (All the time of his separation, \em or of the keeping of his vow\em*, a razor shall not pass over his head, until the days be fulfilled in which he is consecrated, \em or is dedicated\em*, to the Lord; he shall be holy, and his head hair shall grow.)\sls*
\p 
\v 6 In all the time of his hallowing \sls (or In all the time of his consecration, \em or his dedication\em*)\sls*, he shall not enter upon a dead body,
\p 
\v 7 and soothly he shall not be defouled upon the dead body of his father and of his mother, of brother and of sister, for the hallowing of his God is upon his head; \sls (yea, he shall not even be defiled with the dead body of his own father or his mother, or his brother or his sister, for the consecration of his God is upon his head;)\sls*
\p 
\v 8 each day of his separating, \em or avowing\em*, shall be holy to the Lord.
\p 
\v 9 But if any man is dead suddenly before him, the head of his hallowing shall be defouled, which he shall shave anon in the same day of his cleansing, and again in the seventh day; \sls (But if anyone is suddenly dead before him, the hair of his consecration shall be defiled, and he shall shave it off on the day of his cleansing, that is, on the seventh day afterward;)\sls*
\p 
\v 10 forsooth in the eighth day he shall offer two turtles, either two birds of a culver, to the priest, in the entering of the bond of peace of witnessing. \sls (then on the eighth day, he shall offer two turtledoves, or two young pigeons, to the priest, at the entrance to the Tabernacle of the Covenant, \em that is, the Tabernacle of the Witnessing\em*.)\sls*
\p 
\v 11 And the priest shall make, \em or offer\em*, one for sin, and the tother into burnt sacrifice; and the priest shall pray for him, for he sinned upon a dead body, and he shall hallow his head in that day. \sls (And the priest shall offer one of the birds for a sin offering, and the other for a burnt sacrifice, and so the priest shall make amends for him, for he sinned through contact with a dead body; and then he shall consecrate his head again on that day.)\sls*
\p 
\v 12 And he shall hallow to the Lord the days of his separating, and he shall offer a lamb of one year for his sin, so nevertheless that the former days be made void, for his hallowing is defouled. \sls (And he shall rededicate the days of his separation to the Lord, and he shall offer a one-year-old lamb for his sin, nevertheless the former days shall be made void, for the hair of his consecration was defiled.)\sls*
\p 
\v 13 This is the law of hallowing. When the days shall be fulfilled, which he deemed \em to fulfill\em* by a vow, \em the priest\em* shall bring him to the door of the tabernacle of \add [the]\add* bond of peace, \sls (This is the law of consecration, \em or of dedication\em* or This is the law for the Nazarite. And when the days shall be fulfilled, which he committed \em to fulfill\em* by a vow, \em the priest\em* shall bring him to the entrance of the Tabernacle of the Covenant,)\sls*
\p 
\v 14 and he shall offer his offering to the Lord, a lamb of one year without wem, into burnt sacrifice, and a sheep of one year without wem, for sin, and a ram without wem, \sls (as)\sls* a peaceable sacrifice; \sls (and he shall offer his offering to the Lord, a one-year-old lamb without blemish, \em or without fault\em*, for a burnt sacrifice, and a one-year-old sheep without blemish, for a sin offering, and a ram without blemish, for a peace offering;)\sls*
\p 
\v 15 also a basket of therf loaves, that be sprinkled \sls (al)\sls*together with oil, and cakes sodden in water, and after anointed with oil, without sourdough, and \add [the]\add* flowing sacrifices of all \em these\em* by themselves; \sls (and a basket of unleavened bread, that is sprinkled with oil, and cakes made without yeast, boiled in water, and anointed with oil, and the grain and wine offerings for all of \em these\em*;)\sls*
\p 
\v 16 which the priest shall offer before the Lord, and he shall make, \em or offer these\em*, as well for sin as into burnt sacrifice. \sls (which the priest shall offer before the Lord, and he shall offer \em these\em* for his sin offering, and for his burnt sacrifice.)\sls*
\p 
\v 17 Soothly he shall offer the ram \sls (as)\sls* a peaceable sacrifice to the Lord, and he shall offer therewith a basket of therf loaves, and flowing sacrifices, that be due by custom. \sls (And he shall offer the ram as a peace offering to the Lord, and he shall offer a basket of unleavened bread with it, and the grain and wine offerings, that be due by custom.)\sls*
\p 
\v 18 Then the Nazarite, \em or he that is hallowed\em*, shall be shaven from the hair of his hallowing, before the door of the tabernacle of \add [the]\add* bond of peace; and \em the priest\em* shall take his hairs, and he shall put them upon the fire, which is put under the sacrifice of peaceable things. \sls (Then the Nazarite, \em that is, he who is consecrated\em*, shall shave off the hair of his consecration, at the entrance to the Tabernacle of the Covenant; and \em the priest\em* shall take his hair, and he shall put it on the fire which is under the peace offering.)\sls*
\p 
\v 19 And \em he shall take\em* the shoulder sodden of the ram, and one therf cake from the basket, and one \add [thin]\add* therf cake first sodden in water and afterward fried in oil, and he shall betake \em them\em* into the hands of the Nazarite, after that his head is shaven. \sls (And \em he shall take\em* the boiled shoulder of the ram, and one unleavened cake from the basket, and one thin unleavened wafer first boiled in water and then fried in oil, and he shall put \em them\em* into the hands of the Nazarite, after that he hath shaved his head.)\sls*
\p 
\v 20 And the priest shall raise \sls (up)\sls* in the sight of the Lord the things taken again of him. And those things hallowed shall be the priest’s \em part\em*, as the breast which is commanded to be separated, and the hip. After these things the Nazarite may \sls (again)\sls* drink wine. \sls (And then the priest shall take these things from him, and raise them up as a special gift before the Lord. And these consecrated things shall be the priest’s \em portion\em*, including the special gift of the breast, and the special contribution of the leg. And after these things be done, the Nazarite can drink wine again.)\sls*
\p 
\v 21 This is the law of the Nazarite, when he hath avowed his offering to the Lord, in the time of his consecration, \em or hallowing\em*, besides these things which his hand findeth. By this that he \add [hath]\add* avowed in soul, \em or in will\em*, so he shall do, to the perfection of his hallowing. \sls (This is the law for the Nazarite, when he hath vowed his offering to the Lord, at the time of his consecration, besides these things which his hand findeth. By this that he hath vowed with his soul, \em or with his will\em*, so he shall do, to the perfection, \em or the completion\em*, of his dedication.)\sls*
\p 
\v 22 And the Lord spake to Moses and said,
\p 
\v 23 Speak thou to Aaron and to his sons, \sls (and say)\sls*, Thus ye shall bless the sons of Israel \sls (or Thus shall ye bless the Israelites)\sls*, and ye shall say to them,
\p 
\v 24 The Lord bless thee, and keep thee;
\p 
\v 25 the Lord show his face to thee, and have mercy upon thee;
\p 
\v 26 the Lord turn his cheer to thee, and give peace to thee. \sls (the Lord turn his face toward thee, and give peace to thee.)\sls*
\p 
\v 27 They shall call inwardly my name on the sons of Israel, and I shall bless them. \sls (Yea, they shall call my name upon, \em or over\em*, the Israelites, and I shall bless them.)\sls*
\c 7
\cl CHAPTER 7
\p 
\v 1 And it was done in the day in which Moses fulfilled, \em or ended\em*, the tabernacle, and areared it, and anointed it, and hallowed it with all the vessels, \em or instruments\em*, thereof, and the altar \em he hallowed\em* in like manner, and the vessels thereof. \sls (And it was done on the day in which Moses finished the Tabernacle, and raised it up, that he anointed it, and consecrated it, \em or dedicated it\em*, and all of its vessels, \em or its instruments\em*, and the altar, and its vessels.)\sls*
\p 
\v 2 And the princes of Israel, and the heads of families, that were, by all lineages, the sovereigns of them that were numbered, \sls (And the leaders of Israel, that is, the heads of the families, who were, by all the tribes, the rulers of those who were listed, \em or were registered\em*,)\sls*
\p 
\v 3 offered gifts before the Lord, six wains covered, with twelve oxen; two dukes offered one wain, and each offered one ox. And they offered those \em wains\em* before the tabernacle. \sls (brought their offerings before the Lord, in six covered wagons, with twelve oxen; two leaders, \em or two chief men\em*, offered one wagon, and each offered one ox. And they brought those \em wagons\em* to the front of the Tabernacle.)\sls*
\p 
\v 4 Soothly the Lord said to Moses,
\p 
\v 5 Take thou of them, that they serve in the service of the tabernacle, and betake thou those things to the deacons, by the order of their service. \sls (Receive thou these gifts from them, to use in service for the Tabernacle, and give thou them to the Levites, according to the order of their service.)\sls*
\p 
\v 6 And so when Moses had taken the wains, and the oxen, he betook them to the deacons. \sls (And so when Moses had received the wagons, and the oxen, he gave them to the Levites.)\sls*
\p 
\v 7 He gave two wains and four oxen to the sons of Gershon, after that \sls (that)\sls* they had need \sls (of)\sls*.
\p 
\v 8 He gave four other wains and eight oxen to the sons of Merari, by their offices and religion \sls (or for their duties and their service)\sls*, under the hand of Ithamar, the son of Aaron, the priest.
\p 
\v 9 Forsooth he gave not wains and oxen to the sons of Kohath, for they serve in the saintuary, and bear the charges with their own shoulders. \sls (But he did not give any wagons or oxen to the sons of Kohath, for they serve in the sanctuary, and carry the loads with their own shoulders.)\sls*
\p 
\v 10 Therefore the dukes offered, in the hallowing of the altar, in the day in which it was anointed, their offering to the Lord, before the altar. \sls (And so the leaders offered, for the dedication of the altar, on the day in which it was anointed, their offering to the Lord, before the altar.)\sls*
\p 
\v 11 And the Lord said to Moses, All the dukes by themselves offer they gifts, by all days by themselves, into the hallowing of the altar. \sls (And the Lord said to Moses, Have all the leaders offer their gifts, one by one, in the days that follow, for the dedication of the altar.)\sls*
\p 
\v 12 Nahshon, the son of Amminadab, \sls (the prince)\sls* of the lineage of Judah, offered his offering in the first day; and \sls (he offered)\sls*\sls (On the first day, Nahshon, the son of Amminadab, the leader of the sons of Judah, offered)\sls*
\p 
\v 13 a silver vessel \em to prove incense and such things\em*, in the weight of an hundred and thirty shekels, a basin of silver, having seventy shekels by the weight of the saintuary, ever either full of \add [tried]\add* flour sprinkled \sls (al)\sls*together with oil, into sacrifice; \sls (a silver vessel, weighing a hundred and thirty shekels, and a silver basin, weighing seventy shekels, by the measure, \em or the standard\em*, of the sanctuary, and each full of fine flour sprinkled with oil, for a grain offering;)\sls*
\p 
\v 14 a spoon of ten golden shekels, full of incense. \sls (and a gold saucer, weighing ten shekels, full of incense.)\sls*
\p 
\v 15 \em He offered\em* an ox of the drove, and a ram, and a lamb of one year, into burnt sacrifice; \sls (\em And he offered\em* an ox from the herd, and a ram, and a one-year-old lamb, for a burnt sacrifice;)\sls*
\p 
\v 16 and a buck of \sls (the)\sls* goats, for sin. \sls (and a goat buck, for a sin offering.)\sls*
\p 
\v 17 And \em he offered\em* in the sacrifice of peaceable things, twain oxen, five rams, five goat bucks, five lambs of one year. This is the offering of Nahshon, the son of Amminadab. \sls (And for a peace offering, \em he offered\em* two oxen, five rams, five goat bucks, and five one-year-old lambs. This was the offering of Nahshon, the son of Amminadab.)\sls*
\p 
\v 18 In the second day, Nethaneel, the son of Zuar, duke of the lineage of Issachar, offered \sls (On the second day, Nethaneel, the son of Zuar, the leader of the sons of Issachar, offered)\sls*
\p 
\v 19 a silver vessel \em to prove incense and such things\em*, weighing an hundred and thirty shekels, a silver basin, having seventy shekels by the weight of the saintuary, ever either full of \add [tried]\add* flour sprinkled \sls (al)\sls*together with oil, into sacrifice; \sls (a silver vessel, weighing a hundred and thirty shekels, and a silver basin, weighing seventy shekels, by the measure of the sanctuary, and each full of fine flour sprinkled with oil, for a grain offering;)\sls*
\p 
\v 20 a golden spoon, having ten shekels, full of incense; \sls (a gold saucer, weighing ten shekels, full of incense;)\sls*
\p 
\v 21 an ox of the drove, and a ram, and a lamb of one year, into burnt sacrifice; \sls (an ox from the herd, and a ram, and a one-year-old lamb, for a burnt sacrifice;)\sls*
\p 
\v 22 and a buck of \sls (the)\sls* goats, for sin. \sls (and a goat buck, for a sin offering.)\sls*
\p 
\v 23 And in the sacrifice of peaceable things \em he offered\em* twain oxen, five rams, five goat bucks, five lambs of one year. This was the offering of Nethaneel the son of Zuar. \sls (And for a peace offering, \em he offered\em* two oxen, five rams, five goat bucks, and five one-year-old lambs. This was the offering of Nethaneel the son of Zuar.)\sls*
\p 
\v 24 In the third day \sls (or On the third day)\sls*, Eliab, the son of Helon, the prince of the sons of Zebulun, offered
\p 
